!import-table --CRIT_Slashing --show
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Slash! Deal the maximum result of your damage dice twice, receive a Wound point, and the creature is bleeding. For the next minute the creature loses 4 times the amount of blood at the start of each of its turns until it uses an action to staunch this wound. --1 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Dissected! Deal twice the maximum result of your damage dice and receive a Wound point. --1 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Severed! Deal the maximum amount of damage from your normal damage dice then roll your damage dice and add the result. Then roll on the Minor Injury chart. If the creature is wearing light or no armor roll on the Lingering Injury chart instead. --1 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Lacerated! Roll your damage dice twice and add them together and the creature is bleeding. For the next minute the creature loses 3 times the amount of blood at the start of each of its turns until it uses an action to staunch this wound. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Deep slice! Roll your damage dice twice and add them together and the creature is bleeding. For the next minute the creature loses double the blood at the start of each of its turns until it uses an action to staunch this wound. --1 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Great hit! Roll your damage dice twice and add them together --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Open gash! Roll your damage dice as normal and the creature is bleeding s until it uses an action to staunch this wound. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Good hit! Do not roll your damage dice, instead deal the maximum result possible with those dice. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Slashing --Sliced and diced! Roll damage as normal and the creature loses 1d6 hit points at the start of its next turn. --2 --
